ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT:
An evaporator is fed with 15000 kg/h of a solution containing 10% NaCl, 15% NaOH and rest water. In the operation, water is evaporated and NaCl is precipitated as crystals. The thick liquor leaving the evaporator contains 45% NaOH, 2% NaCl and rest water. The amount of salt precipitated is ________ (in kg/h).

[Rounded off to nearest integer]
A sample of caustic soda flakes contains 74.6% Na2O by weight. What is the purity of flakes?
In production of sulphur trioxide, 200 kmol of SO2 and 200 kmol of O2 are fed to a reactor. If the percent conversion of SO2 is 75, what are the composition of the product stream on mole basis?
A sample of gas having volume of 1 m3 is compressed to half of its original volume. The operation is carried for a fixed mass of gas at constant temperature. What is the percent increase in pressure?

Wet solid containing 60% water and 40% solids are to be dried to get solids with 10% water by weight. Fresh air contains 0.010 kg water vapour per kg dry air and the air leaving the dryer contains 0.05 kg water vapour per kg dry air. If 100 kg dry air enters the dryer for every kg of dry solids, the quantity of fresh air is ________ (in kg). [Rounded off to nearest integer]
20 g of caustic soda is dissolved in water to prepare 500 ml of solution. What is the normality of solution?

A sample of gas having volume of 10 at 101.325 kPa pressure and at temperature of 298 K is compressed to a high pressure so that its volume reduces by 4.5 l. If the pressure rises by 0.1 MPa, what will be the rise in temperature?

1000 kg of wet solid containing 70% solid by weight are fed to a tray dryer where it is dried by hot air. The product finally obtained is found to contain 1% moisture by weight, the kg of water removed from wet solids is ________. [Rounded off two decimal places]

Ammonia is produced by the following reaction:

The kg of ammonia produced per hour is ________ (rounded of one decimal places) if percent conversion is 25 and nitrogen feed rate is 25 kmol/h.
Which of the following statements is/are correct?
ENGLISH.OPT1: Heat of solidification is the negative of the heat of fusion.
ENGLISH.OPT2: Heat of condensation is the negative of the heat of vaporization.
ENGLISH.OPT3: Heat of fusion is the enthalpy change for the phase transition of melting.
ENGLISH.OPT4: Latent heat of vaporization is the enthalpy change for the phase transition of a vapour to a liquid.

ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT: 2000 ml solution of strength 0.5 N H2SO4 is to be prepared in laboratory by adding 98% H2SO4 (sp.gr. 1.84) to water. What is the volume in ml of 98% H2SO4 to be added to get solution of required strength?

Chlorinated diphenyl is heated from 313 K to 533 K in an indirectly fired heater at the rate of 5000 kg/h. The heat required to be added to the fluid in the heater is ________ (in kW) [Rounded off to nearest integer]. The heat capacity of the fluid in this temperature range is given by equation below:
C = 0.7511 + 1.465 × 10–3 T kJ/kg.K where T is in K
In manufacture of sulphur trioxide, feed to a reactor consist 100 kmol SO2 and 300 kmol air. What is the percentage excess air is used?

A tray dryer is fed with 600 kg of wet ortho nitroaniline containing 10% water. The dried product contains 99.5% ortho nitroaniline (ONA) and the rest water. The percentage of original water that removed in the dryer is ________. [Round off two decimal places]
Nitric acid and water forms maximum boiling azeotrope containing 62.2% water by mole. What is the composition of HNO3 in the azeotrope in weight percentage?

Propane is dehydrogenated to form propylene in a catalytic reactor:

The process is to be designed for 95% overall conversion of propane. The reaction products are separated into two streams. The first, which contains H2, C3H6 and 0.555% of the propane (mole basis) that leaves the reactor, is taken off as product; the second stream, which contains the balance of the unreacted propane and 5% of the propylene in the product stream (on mole basis) is recycled to the reactor. The recycle ratio is ________. [Rounded off to nearest integer]

Dryer system handles 1000 kg/day of wet solids. Wet solids containing 50% solids and 50% water are fed to the first dryer. From the first dryer the product that comes out has 20% moisture. This is admitted to the second dryer from which the product coming out has 2% moisture. Which of the following statements is/are correct?
ENGLISH.OPT1: Percentage of original water removed in the first dryer is 75.
ENGLISH.OPT2: Percentage of original water removed in the second dryer is 23.
ENGLISH.OPT3: Weight of final product is 510.20 kg.
ENGLISH.OPT4: Weight of final product is 375 kg.

ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT: The combustion of 4.73 kg of a sample of coal yielded 5.30 m3 of carbon dioxide gas measured at NTP. What is the carbon content of the sample?
Which of the following statements is/are correct?
ENGLISH.OPT1: Higher heating value (HHV) is defined as value of negative heat of combustion when the product water is a liquid.
ENGLISH.OPT2: Isochoric process is one which describe a system for which pressure is constant.
ENGLISH.OPT3: Latent heat is the heat involved when any phase transition occurs.
ENGLISH.OPT4: A fuel is a substance which burns to produce energy.

ENGLISH.QUESTION_TEXT: In manufacture of acetic acid by oxidation of acetaldehyde, 100 kmol of acetaldehyde is fed to a reactor per hour. The product leaving the reaction contains 15% acetaldehyde, 60% acetic acid, and rest oxygen (on mole basis). What is the percentage conversion of acetaldehyde?

It is desired to have a mixed acid containing 40% HNO3, 43% H2SO4 and 17% H2O by weight.
Sulphuric acid of 98% by weight is readily available. The weight ratio of sulphuric acid to nitric acid is ________. [Rounded off two decimal places]

Acrylonitrile is produced in the reaction of propylene, ammonia and oxygen:

The feed contains 10.0 mol % propylene, 15.0% ammonia and rest air. A fractional conversion of 40% of the limiting reactant is achieved. The molar amounts of O2 in the product stream is ________. [Rounded off one decimal places] Taking 100 mol of feed as a basis.

A sample of coal is found to contain 65% carbon and 22% ash on weight basis. The analysis of refuse after combustion shows 7% carbon and rest ash. The percentage of the original carbon unburnt in the refuse is ________. [Rounded off two decimal places]
The carbon monoxide is reacted with hydrogen to produce methanol. Which of the following statements is/are correct?
ENGLISH.OPT1: The stoichiometric ratio of H2 to CO is 2.
ENGLISH.OPT2: The weight ratio of CO to H2 is 7, if both are fed to reactor in stoichiometric proportion.
ENGLISH.OPT3: The quantity of CO required to produce 1000 kg of CH3OH is 875 kg.
ENGLISH.OPT4: The stoichiometric ratio of H2 to CO is 4.

(in KJ) [Rounded off two decimal places]. Using the mean molal heat capacity

Orsat analysis of a flue gas gives the following composition by volume :
CO2 : 13.4%, O2 : 6.2% and rest N2
What is the percentage excess air involved in the combustion reaction?

The reaction between ethylene and hydrogen bromide to form ethylene bromide is carried out in a continuous reactor. The product stream from the reactor is analyzed and found to contain 55 mol% ethylene bromide and 35% HBr. The feed to the reactor contains only ethylene and HBr.
The fractional conversion of the limiting reactant is ________. [Rounded off 2 decimal places]

A certain sample of gas at a pressure of 200 kPa is expanded so that its volume is increased by 50%. The operation is done for a fixed mass of gas at constant temperature. What is the final pressure of gas?

A combustion chamber is fed with butane and excess air. Combustion of butane is complete. The composition of combustion gases on volume basis is given below:
CO2 = 9.39%, H2O = 12.73%, O2 = 3.70 and N2 = 74.18% What is the mole ratio of air to butane used?

Formaldehyde produced by dehydrogenation of methanol.

The per pass conversion is 67%. The product leaving the reactor is fed to separation unit battery where formaldehyde is separated from methanol and hydrogen. The separated methanol is recycled to reactor. If the production rate of formaldehyde is 1000 kg/h, the flow rate of methanol required to the process as fresh feed is ________ (in kmol/h). [Rounded off two decimal places]
For a complete combustion of propane what is the percentage excess air fed to the combustion chamber?

Using phase rule, what are the degrees of freedom for each of the following system at equilibrium?
(i) Pure liquid water.
(ii) Pure water at 273.15 K and 4.58 mm Hg.
(iii) A vapor-liquid mixture of four hydrocarbons.
